illness and financial aid i receive financial aid and this term took shorter classes they are only weeks instead of i became sick and due to this had to miss an entire week of the weeks if i fail i wanted to know if my own illness is a strong enough reason to get a hardship and continue to receive financial aid next term you should probably speak to a counselor in the financial aid office about your situation schools are required to monitor your academic progress if you fail to meet the minimum standards then you can be denied additional financial aid however the standards vary from school to school failing one class may or may not remove your eligibility for aid check with the counselor have him her go over your academics and see if your situation will warrant needing to file an appeal Education in the People's Republic of China College admissions Education in the United States Graduate school School counselor Scholarship Probation officer Education in Romania GED Constitution of the Turkish Republic of Northern Cyprus Unemployment W. Mark Felt Warrant Officer No Child Left Behind Act Education in Hong Kong Quizbowl College Redundant array of independent disks Clergy Poker jargon Drowning Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints Education in Japan International Red Cross and Red Crescent Movement Student loan Grade (education) Hopkins School Life insurance Unlawful combatant Information Technology Infrastructure Library Education in Germany United States Naval Academy Health insurance Driver's license Single Convention on Narcotic Drugs Baseball Involuntary commitment Contract 2005 Kashmir earthquake United Nations Relief and Works Agency for Palestine Refugees in the Near East Insurance Drill instructor Annuity Credit card Airport Hunter College High School Standard Mandarin U.S. presidential election, 2004 Library (computer science) Betting (poker) Church of Christ, Scientist UK Singles Chart Online Copyright Infringement Liability Limitation Act School bus Ac